      "comment": "HAPPY TOO YA (2) has been hard to fault of late and made it two wins in a row when successful at his latest appearance over this distance, leading from this barrier and getting home by 4 metres. Takes another step up in grade but should go forward again so can land the hat trick. REFUSAL (8) resumes after good success last prep, winning on three occasions. Has scored fresh before and should be ready to go after placing in two recent trials. CAPTAIN BART (7) was solid after racing parked last time and did a good job for second after racing parked two back. ONE FOR THE RODI (9) enjoys a class drop on the last outing. Won in similar grade at Newcastle last month so may be competitive.",
